issue.title: can not connect to mongodb
issue.body:
###mongo version cause this bug?
sorry,my English is poor.i try my best to explain this question
```
//i have install below software
rvm install 1.9.3
yum  -y  install rubygems
yum  -y install ruby-devel
gem install em-resolv-replace
gem install json
gem install bson_ext
gem install mongo
gem install rchardet

//then test on two  centos  server( x64 and x86 centos ).but meet the same bug
[root@cluster whatweb]#  ruby -v
ruby 1.9.3p551 (2014-11-13 revision 48407) [x86_64-linux]
[root@cluster whatweb]# ps -aux |grep mongo
Warning: bad syntax, perhaps a bogus '-'? See /usr/share/doc/procps-3.2.8/FAQ
root     22988  146  0.2 642984 73976 ?        Sl   14:32  19:10 /usr/local/mongodb/bin/mongod --dbpath=/usr/local/mongodb/data/db --logpath=/usr/local/mongodb/logs/mongodb.log --fork
root     23242  0.0  0.0 105292   864 pts/2    S+   14:45   0:00 grep mongo
[root@cluster whatweb]# whatweb *** --log-mongo-database local --log-mongo-host 127.0.0.1 --log-mongo-collection whatweb --log-mongo-username=whatweb --log-mongo-password='pass' -p +./plugins-disabled/Charset.rb
/public/home/***/whatweb/lib/output.rb:653:in `initialize': uninitialized constant Mongo::Connection (NameError)
	from /public/home/***/whatweb/whatweb:879:in `new'
	from /public/home/***/whatweb/whatweb:879:in `<main>'

```
same situation.
<http://stackoverflow.com/questions/12511699/mongoid-uninitialized-constant-mongo-nameerror>
<http://stackoverflow.com/questions/30431059/uninitialized-constant-mongoconnection>

comment.body:
Well, I found part of the answer I was looking for. In my case, gem install mongo installed v2 of the driver. I'm not using it for anything else, so I did the following:
```sh
$ sudo gem uninstall  mongo  --version 2.2.4
$ sudo gem install  mongo  --version 1.12.5
```

After fixing the driver version, WhatWeb worked as expected.

FYI I'm using Mongo 2.4.10 on Debian Stable (Jessie).
